Star Trek CCG First Contact:
an expanding expansion

------------
by Rich Loftus
------------

May 22 1997 - Based on the most popular and
critically acclaimed Star Trek film in light
years, Star Trek: First Contact is the
foundation for Star Trek Customizable Card
Game's upcoming expansion, due in late
summer.

Originally conceived as a 90 card expansion,
Warren Holland and Decipher's product
development team have decided to fully
develop the characters and gameplay elements
of First Contact by adding 40 cards to the
expansion, making it a full 130 cards.

Of the 130 cards of the limited edition First
Contact, 50 will be rare, 40 uncommon and 40
common. Each 9 card pack will contain 1 rare,
3 uncommon and 5 common cards. The 9 card
packs will be shipped with 30 boosters per
display box.

First Contact will introduce the Borg
Collective affiliation, as well as time
travel, and will contain the Enterprise-E,
Zefram Cochrane, and the Vulcans.

Check out the preliminary First Contact
expansion art in the Star Trek Future History
exhibit in The Galleries.

